{"questionId":"9077032","questionHtml":"<p>The time taken for Mars to revolve on its axis is 8.9 × 10<sup>4</sup>&nbsp;s. Calculate, in m s<sup>–1</sup>,&nbsp;the orbital speed of the satellite.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{R^3} = \\frac{{{T^2}}}{k} = \\frac{{{{\\left( {8.9 \\times {{10}^4}} \\right)}^2}}}{{9.25 \\times {{10}^{ - 13}}}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>R</mi>\n      <mn>3</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>T</mi>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mi>k</mi>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>(</mo>\n              <mrow>\n                <mn>8.9</mn>\n                <mo>×</mo>\n                <mrow>\n                  <msup>\n                    <mrow>\n                      <mn>10</mn>\n                    </mrow>\n                    <mn>4</mn>\n                  </msup>\n                </mrow>\n              </mrow>\n              <mo>)</mo>\n            </mrow>\n          </mrow>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>9.25</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>10</mn>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mo>−</mo>\n            <mn>13</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp; <em>R</em> = 2.04&nbsp;× 10<sup>7</sup>&nbsp;«m»&nbsp;✔</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>v</em> = «<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\omega r = \\frac{{2\\pi&nbsp; \\times 2.04 \\times {{10}^7}}}{{89000}} = \">\n  <mi>ω</mi>\n  <mi>r</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n      <mi>π</mi>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>2.04</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>10</mn>\n          </mrow>\n          <mn>7</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>89000</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n</math></span>» 1.4&nbsp;× 10<sup>3</sup>&nbsp;«m s<sup>–1</sup>»</p>\n<p><em><strong>OR</strong></em></p>\n<p><em>v</em>&nbsp;=&nbsp;«<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\sqrt {\\frac{{GM}}{R}}&nbsp; = \\sqrt {\\frac{{6.67 \\times {{10}^{ - 11}} \\times 6.4 \\times {{10}^{23}}}}{{2.04 \\times {{10}^7}}}}&nbsp; = \">\n  <msqrt>\n    <mfrac>\n      <mrow>\n        <mi>G</mi>\n        <mi>M</mi>\n      </mrow>\n      <mi>R</mi>\n    </mfrac>\n  </msqrt>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <msqrt>\n    <mfrac>\n      <mrow>\n        <mn>6.67</mn>\n        <mo>×</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <msup>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>10</mn>\n            </mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mn>11</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </msup>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>×</mo>\n        <mn>6.4</mn>\n        <mo>×</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <msup>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>10</mn>\n            </mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>23</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </msup>\n        </mrow>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mn>2.04</mn>\n        <mo>×</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <msup>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>10</mn>\n            </mrow>\n            <mn>7</mn>\n          </msup>\n        </mrow>\n      </mrow>\n    </mfrac>\n  </msqrt>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n</math></span>»&nbsp;1.4&nbsp;× 10<sup>3</sup>&nbsp;«m s<sup>–1</sup>»&nbsp;✔</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9077032","referenceCode":"18N.2.HL.TZ0.b.ii","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"The time taken for Mars to revolve on its axis is 8.9 × 104 s. Calculate, in m s–1, the orbital speed of the satellite.","paper":"2","level":"HL","qu